[1] Saudi Arabia: 2 new cases, 1 recovery - MOH 6-7 Nov 2014
Date: Thu-Fri 6-7 Nov 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/ccc/pressreleases/pages/default.aspx?PageIndex=1


As of 12 noon today (7 Nov 2014) there have been a total of:
798 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV including
338 deaths
440 recovered cases and
19 currently active cases

Information on newly laboratory confirmed cases (reported 7 Nov 2014):
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2014-11-07-001.aspx

1 - Riyadh: 45 year old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition, history of pre-existing co-morbidities, no history of contact with animals, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in hospital/clinics, history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in the community
2 - Jeddah: 49 year old expat male, non-healthcare worker, currently in critical condition, no history of co-morbidities, history of contact with animals currently under investigation, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in hospital/clinics, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in the community.

Information on newly reported recovery (reported 6 Nov 2014):
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2014-11-06-001.aspx

Riyadh: 54 year old expat male, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There have now been a total of 798 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infections including 338 deaths (case fatality rate 42.4 percent) reported by Saudi Arabia since June 2012. Of the 2 new cases reported today [7 Nov 2014], one gives a possible history of animal exposure (it is currently under investigation), while the other gives a history of contact with a suspected or confirmed case in the community. The newly reported recovered case is a 54 year old expat male from Riyadh who had been reported as a laboratory confirmed case on 29 Oct 2014 and had a history of contact with a suspected or confirmed case in the community.

Maps showing the location of confirmed cases, recoveries, and deaths can be found with each MOH report at http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/default.aspx. - Mod.MPP]

